{{Quote|A lot of actors dream of being involved with a film at the end of their career that inspires people, and makes a lot of people happy. I got to start my career with a film like that.|William Hootkins|<ref name="Rebel Pilot Reunion">{{InsiderCite|32|Rebel Pilot Reunion}}</ref>}}
'''William Hootkins''' ([[July 5]], [[1940s#1948|1948]]&ndash;[[October 23]], [[2005]]) was a stage and screen actor, who portrayed [[Jek Tono Porkins]] in [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''A New Hope'']].

Hootkins appeared in two other Lucasfilm productions: He portrayed [[W:c:indianajones:Eaton|Major Eaton]] in [[1981]]'s [[Wikipedia:Raiders of the Lost Ark|''Raiders of the Lost Ark'']] (alongside [[Harrison Ford]]), and Diaghilev in the [[1992]] episode "Barcelona, May 1917" of [[Wikipedia:The Young Indiana Jones Chronicles|''The Young Indiana Jones Chronicles'']].

Hootkins is also remembered for his role as Gotham City police lieutenant Max Eckhardt in the 1989 film ''Batman,'' which featured [[Billy Dee Williams]] as Harvey Dent.

Hootkins died of pancreatic cancer in [[Wikipedia:Santa Monica, California|Santa Monica, California]] on October 23, 2005.

